# Manual Governance Rule

Use `doc/manuals-index.md` as the registry of project manuals and their owning maintenance rules.
Treat manuals as living specification in line with `.cursor/rules/manuals-as-specification.mdc`.

## End-of-step checklist (substantial work only)

- Determine which manuals are impacted by the current changes.
- For each impacted manual, apply its dedicated maintenance rule.
- If a manual has no dedicated maintenance rule yet, create one in `.cursor/rules/`.
- Keep setup instructions centralized in `doc/setup-manual.qmd`; do not duplicate setup details in other manuals.
- If manuals or rules are added/renamed/removed, update `doc/manuals-index.md` in the same step.

## Governance constraints

- Prefer focused rules per manual over one large combined manual rule.
- `doc/architecture-manual.qmd` is exempt from the minimal-overlap constraint: it is the one-stop technical reference and may contain all technical explanation for the project, even where topics also appear briefly elsewhere.
